                  NOTE: ENGL 1100 fulfills the new writing requirement in the Faculty of Arts at UBC. Students not entering UBC's Faculty of Arts should take ENGL 1127 or ENGL 1128 instead of ENGL 1100.

Students planning to enrol in a first-semester English course must take the Langara English Test (LET) or Language Proficiency Index Test (LPI) prior to the semester in which they want to register. Students with 80% or above in BC English 12 or BC Literature 12 do not need to write the LET/LPI.

Students who have scored a level 3 on the LET are also strongly encouraged to register in English 1121 in order to upgrade their reading and writing skills.
